Interface PersistentDataContainer

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultPersistentDataContainer

    public interface PersistentDataContainer
extends java.io.Serializable
    Container that may hold data saved from previous sessions..

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      java.io.Serializable get()

      the type of the data in this container.

    • Method Detail

      • get

        java.io.Serializable get()
        Returns:
        data that is in this container, or null if there is no data. This data may have been saved earlier through put, or may be a fixed data object. See getPersistentDataType() to see the type of this container

      • put

        void put(java.io.Serializable data)
        Parameters:
        data - the data to save for the next time. If not null, this data may be saved and delivered back to the party the next time it runs. Only allowed for containers of type PersistentDataType.SERIALIZABLE.

      • getPersistentDataType

        PersistentDataType getPersistentDataType()
        the type of the data in this container. Data put in this container may be saved, depending on this.
